{
  "doc_id": "50145",
  "text": "In livestock, several approaches have been proposed to take into account LD information within LA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ]. These methods model the process generating LD among the putative QTL and the surrounding markers; this process can quickly become unmanageable in the general case [CITATION_4] , and even difficult to approximate [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Extensions of LD models to include LA (that is, the cosegregation of markers and QTL due to physical linkage) are cumbersome for the general case [CITATION_8] or restricted to certain pedigree structures like half-sibs families (C. Cierco, pers. comm.). The parameters of LD generating processes can be either estimated from the data, which is often difficult, or fixed a priori which is unsatisfactory. The existence or not of these events in the past history of a population is unknown. Therefore the validity of any assumptions is largely unknown.",
